    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Two modes of DeepION, denoted as COL and ISO, are designed for the cases of regular colocalized ions from different molecules and isotope ions from the same molecule, respectively. As modality-specific data augmentation is critical to the performance of models trained by contrastive learning, we propose two data augmentation strategies especially for the COL and ISO mods by considering the characteristics of the Poisson distribution and missing patterns in MSI.",
      "asbval:note": "Research question is directly supported by the paper's stated design of two distinct augmentation modes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What are the specific augmentation operations applied in the COL and ISO modes of the DeepION data augmentation pipeline T, and how do they differ?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:54:18.325607+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The original ion image x is first imported into the data augmentation module T to generate two augmented images x1 and x2, where the TCOL, including color jitter, filtering, Poisson noise, and a random missing value, is carried in the COL mode",
      "asbval:note": "COL mode produces two augmented images (x1 and x2) from original image x.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Two augmented ion images from COL mode augmentation pipeline",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:54:18.325607+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "while TISO introduces an additional process for the intensity-dependent missing value in ISO mode",
      "asbval:note": "ISO mode also produces two augmented images but with additional intensity-dependent missing value operation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Two augmented ion images from ISO mode augmentation pipeline",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:54:18.325607+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The encoder module is used to learn an ion image representation function f(\u2022|\u03b8f) to extract the high-level features from ion images for downstream tasks. It consists of twin networks that share identical parameters and adopt the pretrained Resnet18 as the backbone network",
      "asbval:note": "ResNet18 is used as the backbone network in the encoder module, not directly in the data augmentation module. However, it is part of the overall DeepION architecture.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ResNet18",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:54:18.325607+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the TCOL, including color jitter, filtering, Poisson noise, and a random missing value, is carried in the COL mode",
      "asbval:note": "Color jitter is explicitly listed as part of COL mode augmentation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
