    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The encoder module is used to learn an ion image representation function f(\u2022|\u03b8f) to extract the high-level features from ion images for downstream tasks. It consists of twin networks that share identical parameters and adopt the pretrained Resnet18 as the backbone network (Figure S2A). Taking the ion image x as an example, the encoder takes two augmented views x1 and x2 from ion image x as inputs. Then, two ion image representations r1 (d = 512) and r2 (d = 512) corresponding to the same image x are obtained",
      "asbval:note": "Exact match: shared-weight ResNet18 encoders processing two augmented views to produce 512-dimensional vectors.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
