    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The target of projection is to learn a multilayer perceptron (MLP) function g(\u2022|\u03b8g) to ensure that the econder module outputs a meaningful ion image representation. Here, the projection module consists of three fully connected (FC) layers... The target of prediction is to learn an MLP function to avoid the model producing the collapse results. It consists of two FC layers... Taking the ion image x as an example, the encoder takes two augmented views x1 and x2 from ion image x as inputs. Then, two ion image representations r1 (d = 512) and r2 (d = 512) corresponding to the same image x are obtained",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the Projection and Prediction modules operating on 512-dimensional encoder outputs and their role in preventing collapse during contrastive learning.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
