    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/convolutional-neural-network-encoding/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The encoder module is used to learn an ion image representation function f(\u2022|\u03b8f) to extract the high-level features from ion images for downstream tasks. It consists of twin networks that share identical parameters and adopt the pretrained Resnet18 as the backbone network... Taking the ion image x as an example, the encoder takes two augmented views x1 and x2 from ion image x as inputs. Then, two ion image representations r1 (d = 512) and r2 (d = 512) corresponding to the same image x are obtained",
      "asbval:note": "Exact match: shared-weight ResNet18 encoder, twin networks with identical parameters, processes augmented image pairs (x1, x2), outputs 512-dimensional vectors (r1, r2) for contrastive learning.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "convolutional-neural-network-encoding",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use a shared-weight ResNet18 encoder to transform pairs of augmented ion images into fixed 512-dimensional representation vectors for contrastive learning.",
