      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ion-image-augmentation-design/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Two modes of DeepION, denoted as COL and ISO, are designed for the cases of regular colocalized ions from different molecules and isotope ions from the same molecule, respectively. As modality-specific data augmentation is critical to the performance of models trained by contrastive learning, we propose two data augmentation strategies especially for the COL and ISO mods by considering the characteristics of the Poisson distribution and missing patterns in MSI.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported; paper explicitly describes COL/ISO modes, mode-specific augmentation, and contrastive learning framework.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ion-image-augmentation-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Design and apply mode-specific data augmentation pipelines (COL and ISO) to ion images for mass spectrometry imaging to generate contrastive pairs while preserving domain-relevant physical properties. The choice of augmentation mode and composition depends on the ion relationship",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:57:57.482588+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ion-image-augmentation-design/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The encoder module is used to learn an ion image representation function f(\u2022|\u03b8f) to extract the high-level features from ion images for downstream tasks. It consists of twin networks that share identical parameters and adopt the pretrained Resnet18 as the backbone network",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed; ResNet18 used as encoder backbone for 512-dimensional representation vectors.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
