    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ion-image-augmentation-design/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "a modality-specific data augmentation strategy is designed by incorporating the characteristics of MSI data (detailed descriptions seen in Material S1), including color jitter, filtering, Poisson noise, random missing value, and intensity-dependent missing value (Figure 2). Here, color jitter and filtering are commonly used in natural images to make the model insensitive to the brightness of images and concentrate on the critical features.",
      "asbval:note": "Supported; color jitter is listed as part of augmentation strategy. Order of operations confirmed in Figure 1 description.",
