    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ion-image-embedding-optimization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The encoder module is used to learn an ion image representation function f(\u2022|\u03b8f) to extract the high-level features from ion images for downstream tasks... two ion image representations r1 (d = 512) and r2 (d = 512) corresponding to the same image x are obtained... The target of projection is to learn a multilayer perceptron (MLP) function g(\u2022|\u03b8g) to ensure that the encoder module outputs a meaningful ion image representation... The target of prediction is to learn an MLP function to avoid the model producing the collapse results.",
      "asbval:note": "Claim is fully supported by passage describing the 512-dimensional outputs, projection module for meaningful representation, and prediction module to prevent collapse.",
