    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neural-network-projection-module-design/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The target of projection is to learn a multilayer perceptron (MLP) function g(\u2022|\u03b8g) to ensure that the econder module outputs a meaningful ion image representation. Here, the projection module consists of three fully connected (FC) layers... The target of prediction is to learn an MLP function to avoid the model producing the collapse results. It consists of two FC layers... To prevent the DeepION model from collapsing, we use the stop gradient operation during the model training.",
      "asbval:note": "Verbatim presence and semantic equivalence confirmed. Paper explicitly describes projection and prediction modules designed to prevent collapse.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "neural-network-projection-module-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Design and implement Projection and Prediction modules that transform high-dimensional encoder outputs into lower-dimensional spaces suitable for contrastive learning while preventing representation collapse.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:36.982790+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neural-network-projection-module-design/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DeepION, a novel deep learning-based method designed specifically for ion image representation, which is applied to the identification of colocalized ions and isotope ions. In DeepION, contrastive learning is introduced to ensure that the model can generate the ion image representation in a self-supervised manner without manual annotation.",
      "asbval:note": "Semantic equivalence: paper confirms self-supervised learning on ion images and the need to prevent collapse via contrastive learning design.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "neural-network-projection-module-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential when training self-supervised models on ion images or similar high-dimensional data where trivial solutions (uniform representations) must be actively avoided.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:36.982790+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neural-network-projection-module-design/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Taking the ion image x as an example, the encoder takes two augmented views x1 and x2 from ion image x as inputs. Then, two ion image representations r1 (d = 512) and r2 (d = 512) corresponding to the same image x are obtained",
      "asbval:note": "Verbatim presence: 512-dimensional outputs from paired encoders on augmented ion images explicitly stated.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "neural-network-projection-module-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have 512-dimensional representation vectors output from paired encoders processing augmented versions of the same input (e.g., ion images in mass spectrometry imaging)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:36.982790+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neural-network-projection-module-design/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DeepION is composed with the data augmentation module, encoder module, projection module, prediction module, and dimensionality reduction module... The target of projection is to learn a multilayer perceptron (MLP) function g(\u2022|\u03b8g)... A contrasting loss is employed to maximize the similarity with a stop-gradient operation on h2",
      "asbval:note": "Semantic equivalence: workflow diagram and description confirm projection/prediction modules operate between encoder and contrastive loss computation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "neural-network-projection-module-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill as part of the training pipeline after the Encoder module but before computing contrastive loss.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:36.982790+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
